<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4231] Flush regions in multiple threads</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4231</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As servers get beefier, it makes less and less sense to have only a single thread do flushes at a time. In watching an insert-only benchmark run, HBase isn&apos;t currently disk, network, or CPU-bound &amp;#8211; it seems it&apos;s bound only by the rate at which flushes and compactions get processed. Increasing the threading a bit here should increase total disk/network throughput utilization.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
